                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9435: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-19T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 19, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Your 448 of August 16, 3 p.m., and Tokyo’s 278 of August 18, 5 p.m.<note
                        n="61" xml:id="d266fn61">Neither printed.</note> In view of large number of
                    Americans at Kuling and of Japanese Navy Department’s instruction to Japanese
                    naval forces to refrain from bombing Kuling unless it is used as a base for
                    Chinese military operations, please ask Chinese authorities to refrain from
                    military operations which would be likely to bring hostilities into the
                    neighborhood of Kuling.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
